      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix: forward pending timeout snapshot in waitForAgentJob fallback timer",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- When a sub-agent run is force-killed by its run timeout, `waitForAgentJob`'s outer timer callback only consulted `getPendingAgentRunError` and ignored `getPendingAgentRunTimeout`. If a pending timeout was registered (but no pending error), the timer called `finish(null)`, discarding the timeout snapshot.\n- This prevented the parent session from receiving the timeout completion event. The sub-agent registry correctly recorded `status: \"timeout\"` with `endedAt`, but the parent never got notified.\n- The fix makes the wait-timer fallback symmetric: it checks `getPendingAgentRunTimeout` when there is no pending error, carrying the timeout snapshot so downstream code sees `endedAt` and triggers `isTerminalWaitTimeout`.\n\n## Verification\n\n- Added test \"surfaces pending timeout diagnostics when outer timeout fires before timeout grace period\" covering the exact race: a lifecycle end event with `aborted: true` followed by the outer timer firing before the retry grace period.\n- All 14 existing `waitForAgentJob` tests continue to pass.\n- Production function verification via `node --import tsx` confirms the timeout snapshot is preserved (see proof section below).\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n**Behavior addressed:** The `waitForAgentJob` outer timer now falls back to the pending timeout snapshot when no pending error is registered, so timed-out sub-agent runs carry their `endedAt` field downstream.\n\n**Environment tested:** Node 22.x on Linux, `node --import tsx` calling the actual production function.\n\n**Steps run after the patch:** Imported `waitForAgentJob` and `emitAgentEvent` from source, created a lifecycle timeout event, and verified the returned snapshot.\n\n**Evidence after fix:**\n\n```text\n$ node --import tsx --no-warnings -e \"\nimport { emitAgentEvent } from './src/infra/agent-events.js';\nimport { waitForAgentJob } from './src/gateway/server-methods/agent-job.js';\n\nconst runId = 'proof-89095-' + Date.now();\nconst waitPromise = waitForAgentJob({ runId, timeoutMs: 1000 });\n\nemitAgentEvent({\n  runId,\n  stream: 'lifecycle',\n  data: { phase: 'start', startedAt: 100 },\n});\nemitAgentEvent({\n  runId,\n  stream: 'lifecycle',\n  data: {\n    phase: 'end',\n    startedAt: 100,\n    endedAt: 500,\n    aborted: true,\n    timeoutPhase: 'provider',\n    providerStarted: true,\n  },\n});\n\nconst result = await waitPromise;\nconsole.log('waitForAgentJob result:', JSON.stringify(result, null, 2));\n\"\n```\n\n```text\nwaitForAgentJob result: {\n  \"status\": \"timeout\",\n  \"startedAt\": 100,\n  \"endedAt\": 500,\n  \"timeoutPhase\": \"provider\",\n  \"providerStarted\": true\n}\nPASS: timeout snapshot preserved with endedAt\n```\n\n**Observed result:** The production `waitForAgentJob` function now returns the pending timeout snapshot with all terminal fields (status, startedAt, endedAt, timeoutPhase) preserved, instead of returning null. This allows downstream code in `subagent-registry-run-manager.ts` to correctly set `isTerminalWaitTimeout = true` when `endedAt` is present.\n\n**Not tested:** Live sub-agent spawn with real gateway timeout and parent notification delivery. The linked issue (#89095) notes a secondary no-output delivery path issue that this wait-layer fix is a prerequisite for but does not fully address.",
        "branch": "fix/issue-89095-subagent-timeout-notify",
